 bosses and items that we all know from all the other metal slug games;
- Game currency is very easy and fast to earn so you can upgrade your units and base almost at the same rate you progress on the world map;
- It's easy to get the hang of it after a few minutes of playtime;
- For a free to play tower defense like game it has much more content than many other TD games;

Cons
- There is much P2W stuff in the game and the coolest stuff is only unlocked with real money;
- PVP system takes forever to find an opponent so you'll be limited to the single player campaign;
- Even if the enemies and the scenario keep changing in many levels it feels repetitive after playing for some time;
- The game's ammo system (wich works like energy in many games) takes a long time to refill and without ammo you can't play anything on the world map and are limited to pvp and like said above pvp system takes forever to find an opponent so you have a limited amount of tries before waiting for it to refill before trying your luck again.

I love games where skill is the most important thing in them

